[{"id":"VH927077","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><include href=\"../Passage/VH926683.qti.xml\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\"></include></div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">In another experiment, a small piece of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"M g, solid\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"M g, solid\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>Mg</mtext><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>s</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is weighed, then placed in a flask containing excess <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1 molar H C l, aqueous\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"1 molar H C l, aqueous\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>1</mn><mspace depth=\"0.0ex\" height=\"0.0ex\" width=\"0.4em\"></mspace><mi>M</mi><mspace depth=\"0.0ex\" height=\"0.0ex\" width=\"0.25em\"></mspace><mtext>HCl</mtext><mo>(</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>q</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>. The student wants to determine number of the moles of gas produced. Which of the following is the best way to conduct the experiment for accurate data collection?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VH927077_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<div class=\"stimulus_reference\" xmlns=\"http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/apip/apipv1p0/qtiitem/imsqti_v2p2\" xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><p class=\"passage_para\">A <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"0.50 gram\"><math alttext=\"0.50 gram\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>0.50</mn><mspace depth=\"0.0ex\" height=\"0.0ex\" width=\"0.4em\"></mspace><mtext>g</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> sample of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"M g, solid\"><math alttext=\"M g, solid\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>Mg</mtext><mo>(</mo><mi>s</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> was placed in a solution of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"H C l, aqueous\"><math alttext=\"H C l, aqueous\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>HCl</mtext><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>q</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, where it reacted completely.</p></div></div></div>"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Conducting the experiment at different temperatures to see which generates the most gas</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Completing the entire reaction in a large Erlenmeyer flask of known volume to measure the volume of the gas collected</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Collecting the gas in a eudiometer tube and measuring the volume of the gas collected</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Conducting the reaction in a graduated cylinder and measuring the volume of the gas collected</p>"],"answer":2}]